{"word":"βῶλος","slug":"βῶλος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>βῶλος</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>a lump of earth, a clod</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>gleba</el>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>like <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>gleba, land, ground, soil</el>, <b><a href='S:Moschus'>Mosch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>generally, <i>a lump</i> of anything, <i>a mass</i>, of the sun, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}